<paragraph blockId="38.[806,1421,383,497]" pageId="38" pageNumber="537">
<emphasis box="[806,932,383,404]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="537">Etymology:</emphasis>
The specific epithet is derived from the Latin words 
<emphasis box="[966,1040,413,434]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="537">brevis,</emphasis>
meaning short, and 
<emphasis box="[1307,1421,414,435]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="537">processus,</emphasis>
meaning process, referring to the short processes of the aedeagus.
</paragraph>
